## Analysis of Response A  Response A provides a clear and concise summary of the idea of building more properties on green belt lands as a solution to London's housing crisis. It mentions the potential benefits of this solution, such as bigger and cheaper homes for everyone, and acknowledges the opposition to this idea, specifically from Ann Goddard of Elstree & Borehamwood Greenbelt Society. The summary also includes Sam Bowman's perspective on the potential compromise of differentiating between areas of beauty and intensive farmland.  ## Analysis of Response B  Response B also focuses on the option of building more properties on green belt lands as a solution to London's housing crisis. It provides a more detailed summary of the amount of green belt land within the M25 and its significance, as well as Sam Bowman's perspective on the benefits of building on green belt land.
